   "source": [
    "### Colab Free-Tier Constraints and How This Notebook Handles Them\n",
    "\n",
    "Based on the Colab FAQ, free-tier limits are dynamic (GPU availability, idle timeout, maximum VM lifetime up to about 12h, and possible runtime preemption).\n",
    "This notebook is updated to be fault-tolerant under those constraints:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Persistent artifact root prefers Google Drive when mounted.\n",
    "- Checkpoints are saved frequently using step-based policies.\n",
    "- Each method-task pair writes a run ledger entry after completion.\n",
    "- Resume logic always attempts latest checkpoint before fresh training.\n",
    "- Results are snapshotted to disk after every completed task.\n",
    "- Memory pressure is reduced via conservative defaults and explicit cleanup.\n",
    "\n",
    "Operational rule: if the runtime restarts, re-run setup cells and launch the same experiment cell; resume is automatic.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Notebook Update Plan and Task Checklist\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook now follows a platform-first hardening plan for Windows/Linux and CPU/GPU:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Normalize runtime bootstrapping and environment detection for Colab and local OS targets.\n",
    "2. Enforce secure token resolution (`HF_TOKEN`) from Colab Secrets or OS environment only.\n",
    "3. Validate experiment configuration early (task names, positive step counts, causal intervals).\n",
    "4. Apply platform-aware Trainer defaults (Windows-safe dataloader workers, CPU-safe precision flags).\n",
    "5. Enforce fail-closed Laplace checks (no posterior factors -> hard failure).\n",
    "6. Enforce fail-closed causal checks (no causal paths, no published batches, or no applied weights -> hard failure).\n",
    "7. Keep checkpoint-resume and runtime-state snapshots mandatory for recovery.\n",
    "8. Preserve parity between notebook behavior and shared `src/` modules.\n",
    "\n",
    "Completion criteria for each method-task pair:\n",
    "\n",
    "- LoRA Baseline: train + eval complete and checkpoint produced.\n",
    "- Laplace-LoRA: MAP phase complete plus validated posterior accumulation and finite evidence path.\n",
    "- Causal FT: orchestrator completes with non-zero causal path publication and non-zero causal application metrics."
   ]
