    "### Colab-Specific Recommendations (Read Before Running)\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Use Python 3 + GPU runtime only during training; switch to CPU runtime for analysis-only work.\n",
    "2. Keep one active Colab session for one experiment family at a time (LoRA, then Laplace-LoRA, then Causal FT).\n",
    "3. Keep defaults for stability: BATCH_SIZE=8, GRADIENT_ACCUMULATION_STEPS=2, SAVE_STEPS=100, SAVE_TOTAL_LIMIT=3.\n",
    "4. For unstable sessions, lower SAVE_STEPS to 50 to increase recovery points.\n",
    "5. If runtime disconnects, rerun setup cells first (Cells 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 10, 12, 14), then rerun your experiment run cell (Cell 17, 20, or 23).\n",
    "6. If you hit OOM, set BATCH_SIZE=4 and GRADIENT_ACCUMULATION_STEPS=4, then resume from the latest checkpoint.\n",
    "7. Persist artifacts to mounted Drive paths when available; avoid writing many tiny files to Drive root.\n",
    "8. Re-run Cell 25 at the end to rebuild the final summary from persisted snapshots if needed.\n",
    "\n",
    "For full operational details, see NOTEBOOK_EXECUTION_MANUAL.md in the project root."
